sentence: Looking at options trading activity among components of the Russell 3000 index, there is noteworthy activity today in MicroStrategy Inc. (Symbol: MSTR), where a total volume of 513 contracts has been traded thus far today, a contract volume which is representative of approximately 51,300 underlying shares (given that every 1 contract represents 100 underlying shares).
That number works out to 45.6% of MSTR's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 112,420 shares.
Particularly high volume was seen for the $140 strike put option expiring July 19, 2019 , with 500 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 50,000 underlying shares of MSTR.

Extended Stay America Inc (Symbol: STAY) saw options trading volume of 9,008 contracts, representing approximately 900,800 underlying shares or approximately 45.1% of STAY's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 2.0 million shares.
Particularly high volume was seen for the $20 strike call option expiring April 18, 2019 , with 4,456 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 445,600 underlying shares of STAY.

Below is a chart showing STAY's trailing twelve month trading history, with the $20 strike highlighted in orange:

And Home Depot Inc (Symbol: HD) saw options trading volume of 23,425 contracts, representing approximately 2.3 million underlying shares or approximately 43.4% of HD's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 5.4 million shares.
Especially high volume was seen for the $185 strike put option expiring March 29, 2019 , with 2,062 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 206,200 underlying shares of HD.
